55:41.040 --> 55:42.599
NARRATOR: No one
would've believed,

55:42.680 --> 55:45.035
in the last years
of the 19°'th century

55:45.280 --> 55:47.237
that human affairs
were being watched

55:47.360 --> 55:49.271
from the timeless
worlds of space.

55:50.120 --> 55:52.999
<i>No one could've dreamed
we were being scrutinized,</i>

55:53.080 --> 55:55.993
as someone with a microscope
studies creatures that swarm

55:56.200 --> 55:58.111
and multiply in
a drop of water.

55:58.840 --> 56:02.515
Few men even consider the
possibility of life on other planets,

56:02.840 --> 56:05.753
and yet,
across the gulf of space,

56:05.920 --> 56:08.719
minds immeasurably
superior to ours,

56:08.960 --> 56:11.793
regarded this
earth with envious eyes

56:12.080 --> 56:16.711
and slowly and surely they
drew their plans against us.
